      <div class="row-fluid section1">
	<div class="span5 offset1 asset">
	  <img class="img-polaroid" alt="(c) Jacob Wiebe" src="http://media.tumblr.com/08ae2e864b9cc978e2e37478d8ca201e/tumblr_inline_mmxsqxxjmL1qb4juk.jpg">
	</div>
	<div class="span5 copy">
	  <p>
	    Under the ceaseless watch of the moon a killer prowls the streets of London, the grisly murders somehow inexplicably linked to detective John Grayman. 
	    As he finds his lovers slaughtered one by one he cannot help but wonder if he himself could be the killer, are these nocturnal attacks a result of his own trauma or is something more terrify hunting the streets of London? 
	  </p>
	</div>
      </div>

      <div class="row-fluid section2">
	<div class="span5 offset1 copy copy-right">
	  <p>
	    This series of short films will feature three stand alone stories which fit together as one over arching story of loss and horror.
	    Not only will John's s skills as a detective be tested, but his moral fiber as well. 
	    The killings are in some way tied to his actions and figuring out the pattern is the only way he can stop the killer.
	  </P>
	</div>
	<div class="span5 asset">
	  <img class="img-polaroid" alt="(c) Jacob Wiebe" src="http://media.tumblr.com/d2932b44c77aef2f0cb5d3af81b2cdc3/tumblr_inline_mnowgnlCFB1qb4juk.jpg">
	</div>
      </div>

      <div class="row-fluid section3">
	<div class="span10 offset1 copy">
	  <p>
	    As the story progresses the audience is introduced to two pivotal characters: John's Wife Renee, and his friend Donovan. 
	    Both rely on John to be logical and sober but in the wake of so many killings they are often left wanting. 
	    Through these relationships John is given a choice, to indulge in his baser desires to dull the pain of his past, or to look after his responsibilities. 
	    What neither character understands s traumatic experiences in WWII create needs he cannot control, and his failures are not necessarily his fault.
	    <br><br>
	    As John learns more about the killings, and about himself, the story comes together. 
	    All three episodes fit into a tapestry that reveals the identity of the killer and John's connection to the killings.
	    Then he must decide how far he is willing to go to save the life of his family.
	    <br><br>
	    Following John over the course of many years <b>Devil Dog </b> examines the life of a man trying manage his trauma in a time where PTSD was misunderstood. 
	    This cycle of anger, alcoholism and affairs leads to broken relationships and dire consequences. 
	    In this way the werewolf genre is used to explore social issues of the 1950's while bringing new elements to a classic monster movie archetype. 
	  </p>
	</div>
